		<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent" id="comment-786375">
				<div id="div-comment-786375" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/25783e534f72d30a2480e6fda0c9cbf0?s=80&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/25783e534f72d30a2480e6fda0c9cbf0?s=160&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' />			<cite class="fn">andy brookes</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://tutorialzine.com/2016/01/learn-sass-in-15-minutes/#comment-786375">
			April 22, 2017 at 12:04 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Great concise article<br />
If like me you want  to know a little about sass, your probably going to read about first thing figure out how to use it. Also your probably going to want to play with  sass &amp; bootstrap. Having with other coders who might have pulled there hair out with all the options though i would mention a bit about set up. </p>
<p>If your on Linux such as Slackware , you will have Ruby installed by default  which is good because then you can use gem, which can be used to install software.</p>
<p> $gem install sass</p>
<p>Now with a text editor you can write some of the above article &amp; store the file as main.scss say on your Desktop.<br />
$cd Desktop<br />
To convert it to css you just run<br />
$sass main.scss:main.css</p>
<p>Thats OK with one file but with different install options it all looks like Spagetii with a whole bunch of scss files. I found compass the easiest option &amp; have put a quick install on Twitter here: </p>
<p>https://twitter.com/andybrookestar/status/855096970385518593</p>
<p>The next issue is what to edit &amp; where. Theres two files _bootstrap-variables.scss &amp; styles.scss inside the sass dir. I found the best way is not to edit _bootstrap-variables.scss but to use it as a reference for bootstrap variables that can be overridin them in styles.scss</p>
<p>Basically anything you want to override put it before the @import &quot;bootstrap&quot;; line &amp; any of your own styles put it after the @import &quot;bootstrap&quot;; line </p>
<p>eg // file styles.scss</p>
<p>$gray-base:#001;<br />
// Import Bootstrap for Sass</p>
<p>@import &quot;bootstrap&quot;;</p>
<p>$mycolor:#ff00ff;</p>
<p>p.andy<br />
{<br />
color:$my color;<br />
}</p>
<p>run<br />
$ compass compile &amp; you should see changes</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='http://tutorialzine.com/2016/01/learn-sass-in-15-minutes/?replytocom=786375#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "div-comment-786375", "786375", "respond", "7011" )' aria-label='Reply to andy brookes'>Reply</a></div>
